channel.description: The Basement is the safest place on the planet. We encourage people to come down from the desired high-rise to The Basement. We get real, vulnerable, & honest. This is a space where I want to provide mentorship, & also speak with those of influence. WELCOME TO THE BASEMENT.

In this deeply personal and uplifting episode, Anthony O’Neal opens up to Tim Ross about his past, sharing raw and emotional moments around his divorce and other painful experiences. Tim skillfully leads Anthony through process work, helping him unpack the weight of those memories while offering insight, hope, and healing. Despite the heavy topics, the conversation is filled with moments of laughter, making it a balanced mix of depth, vulnerability, and joy. Together, they dive into real talk on relationships, personal growth, and finding hope in hard seasons, creating an episode that leaves listeners inspired and encouraged.

item.content:encoded:
In this episode, Tim Ross welcomes Dr. Jackie Greene to the show, introducing her as a profound speaker, pastor, mother, and wife. Together, they discuss the importance of vulnerability, obedience to God, and the significance of remaining devoted. Dr. Jackie shares her personal journey of overcoming trauma, personal challenges, and her path to self-acceptance through her relationship with God. She introduces her new 90-day devotional, "Remain in His Love," aimed at helping individuals cultivate a deeper, more consistent relationship with God. Tim and Dr. Jackie delve into deep topics, such as balancing confidence with humility, the discipline required to maintain a spiritual life, and the significance of seeking God's presence daily. They share anecdotes from their own lives, exploring the realities of maintaining faith in difficult times and the importance of spiritual resilience. This heartfelt episode is filled with wisdom, personal revelations, and practical advice for anyone looking to deepen their spiritual journey and remain steadfast in their faith.

In this episode of The Basement, Ivory McDonald sits down with Tim Ross for a deep dive into vulnerability, church hurt, and the often unseen struggles within ministry. Ivory shares her own journey of overcoming a legalistic background, battling depression, and finding solace in being transparent with God. Tim Ross opens up about his vision of 'The Basement,' his experience transitioning from a pastor to a podcaster, and the significance of living authentically. This conversation tackles real-life issues many believers face, offering a refreshing perspective on faith, ministry, and life.

item.content:encoded:
In this episode, Tim Ross and comedian Mike Goodwin discuss the challenges and experiences of performing stand-up comedy. They share personal stories of performing in tough venues, the journey from initial failures to finding success, and the importance of humility and generosity in the comedy world. 

The conversation also touches on the transition from being a comedian to an entrepreneur, the impact of authenticity, and balancing personal fulfillment with business acumen.

Along the way, they highlight the support of loved ones, the power of faith, and the critical need to push all chips to the center of the table for true success.



See Privacy Policy at https://art19.com/privacy and California Privacy Notice at https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info.

Step into The Basement for one of the most candid and inspiring conversations yet as Tim Ross welcomes comedian Ali Siddiq. Ali shares his unapologetic philosophy on life—choosing independence over industry pressures and staying true to his values of integrity, self-respect, and honor. Through powerful stories of his upbringing, family struggles, and the profound loss of his father, Ali reveals the lessons that shaped his path in comedy and beyond. This episode goes beyond the laughs, diving into the importance of community, lasting friendships, and creating meaningful memories with those who matter most. Honest, humorous, and deeply moving, this is Ali Siddiq as you’ve never seen him before—a must-watch for anyone seeking inspiration and authenticity.

item.content:encoded:
Join Tim Ross in a deeply moving and powerful episode as he sits down with gospel music legend Kirk Franklin.

In this heartfelt conversation, Kirk Franklin shares his inspiring upbringing and testimony, while Tim creates a space for vulnerability and open dialogue. Together, they explore the significance of friendships and relationships, the challenges and rewards of ministry, and leading in the gospel music era.

This episode is filled with emotion, honesty, and wisdom, offering a unique glimpse into the lives and experiences of two influential figures in the world of gospel and beyond. Don't miss this extraordinary exchange down in The Basement!

item.content:encoded:
Join our Discord: https://discord.gg/NRHEm73BB4


Sub to The B-Side Channel https://youtube.com/@TheB-SideAPP?si=EImX0JC1F2bBzxlr


Want to financially support The Basement?

https://www.paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=9AJ59T2R2X7VL


LOVE YOU ALL!!! Order my book TODAY: https://www.upsettheworld.com/welcometothebasementbook#Retailer-Links


Apple: Download The B-Side App TODAY: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/b-side-app/id6469474522


Android: Download The B-Side App TODAY: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.bsideapp&hl=en_US


https://linktr.ee/timross


Notes:

22:00 Ps. Mike on brotherhood

23:06 Buffers vs blockades

28:10 Check your inventory. Do you know your inner circle? You’ll know them by what they bear

29:59 Will you bleach/clean out the relationships that are toxic?

31:23 “You like transactions”. Acquaintances vs needful relationships

34:31 Father/Son vs Brotherhood

36:19 Jesus released brothers. The Apostles was a brotherhood. They were released two by two

40:02 Mike on working with Bri

41:38 Some of these n**** need to be uncles or spiritual cousins

44:34 “Because I said so” don’t work no more

46:23 Tim on spiritual amway

52:00 The blessing is in PSALM 1!

53:31 Did you really hear God or did you do it selfishly?

54:30 “If they just trusted me they would have gotten more”

57:00 Mike encouraging pastors to unlearn their “tithing” messages. TRUST & TEACH

59:00 Tim’s cheat code: go to the bathroom

1:00:11 The Bible tells us to give out of compulsion

1:02:07 Are you skipping due process?

1:04:25 “I’m not Mike & he’s not me”

1:05:50 God blesses the real you not who you pretend to be

1:06:58 Mike on stopping examples for a year

1:08:36 Are you committing to the person God has called you to be?

1:09:00 Mike addresses the talk about his jewelry

1:14:30 Tim on his boys suits. “Me is enough”

1:19:00 Mike on his High School experience

1:20:20 They bold in ATL

1:21:50 Get out of your space. The world is so BIG! “When you get exposed- you will walk in confidence.”

1:24:30 You will find out more about God when you see the world

1:26:44 Are you triggered because you’re frustrated that you’re not free like they are?

1:28:24 - 2 Peter 3:15-16

1:33:00 Ephesians 6 - armor of God is front facing not the back

1:37:57 If you want impact you will have to be exposed

1:40:16 Tim on his wine green room experience

1:55:00 Tim raps. “AT THAT TIME”

2:16:30 Mike on Overflow albums

2:35:50 the effort is my job & God’s job is outcome

2:40:50 What am I suppose to do?

2:41:58 If you don’t do something with your gifting, God will bless someone else

2:46:34 Do what God told you to do. Stop trying to get validation from others & basing it on income

2:48:20 Tim on his album from early 2000’s

2:53:42 Romans 15:13

3:02:38 Satan is content with Kanye’s album sitting as #1

3:05:41 Greedy business people

3:06:00 Tim pays for B-Side subscription

3:10:40 Work ethic = sweat equity
